3. Encapsulation

Binding data & methods

private variables + public getters/setters

Why? â†’ Data hiding & security

Real example â†’ User class: username, password



---

4. Inheritance

extends keyword

Single, Multilevel, Hierarchical

What Java does NOT support â†’ Multiple inheritance (from class)

Why? â†’ Diamond problem

What is inherited?

What is NOT inherited? (private members, constructors)



---

5. Polymorphism

Compile-time polymorphism (Method Overloading)

Same method name, different parameters

Rules to overload method

Real example: add(int a, int b) / add(double a, double b)


Runtime polymorphism (Method Overriding)

Same method name, same parameters, different implementation

@Override annotation

Achieved through dynamic method dispatch

Used in Spring Boot Beans & Interfaces



---

6. Abstraction

Hiding implementation

Using interfaces & abstract classes

100% abstraction via Interface

Example: JDBC, Spring Boot services



---

7. Interface vs Abstract Class

Feature	Interface	Abstract Class

Variables	public static final	normal variables allowed
Methods	abstract + default + static	abstract + normal
Multiple inheritance	YES	NO
Constructor	NO	YES



---

8. Why OOP in Real Backend Projects?

All enterprise Java frameworks (Spring, Hibernate) are based on OOP

Controllers, Services, Repositories = Polymorphism

DTO models = Encapsulation

Interfaces = Dependency injection

Inheritance for common functionality



